content: Would be an awesome app, except it keeps glitching and the timer is out.
It would be even nicer if you add sounds to indicate the number of the round. Like 1/6 rounds...
This app is perfect!! No problems and I've been using it for about 2 weeks. It's compliments her workouts so well. I have a Samsung.
Really easy to use and convenient but crashes constantly and there's no way to start back in a specific exercise/round. Really frustrating. Had to restart it like four times in this past workout.
The guiding voice stops midway very annoying...otherwise great app
I love the idea of this app! the only thing is, the countdown stops working mid way through the workout. Sarah if you are reading this, please try to fix it!!

I've been using the app for 8 weeks and the guiding voice over stops midway through the workouts, so if you're not paying close attention to your screen you get all messed up. but the app is easy to use and super practical if you follow Sarah's workout ebooks.
I'm on week 5 and finally made it through one workout without the times glitching. It would be a great app if it didn't keep skipping rounds and talking over itself.
It crashes in the middle of the workout every time I used it. Not worth paying for. There are free interval timers that work SOOO much better. Sorry but I wouldnt spend my money on it

Workouts are great but timer turns itself off mid workout! Timer does make it easier overall but super frustrating when it happens! Make sure to keep track of your reps and sets so that you know how much you still have to do

I like how easy it is to keep time, but the voice doesn't always work. It starts off fine and then stops mid exercise, so I'll be going hard waiting for my 3 second count down, and then look at it and its halfway through the rest... kinda frustrating and defeats the point if you have to constantly keep an eye on your phone
Voice overs still not working after update in may 2020.
I have actually never had any issues/glitches with the app. I think it's really helpful with the workouts
Love this app. Makes it easier for me to time my workouts whether they were Sarah's day's or my own. Makes it easy and convenient üòç
Love it!!
No more glitches, seems to work amazing
My 10min blaster doesn't work, just cuts out and closes the app! How can I fix this please? The other timers work fine.

The app is so handy, but if you aren't in the app sometimes the timer stops counting until you go back into it, so the display can't shut off or you might end out doing a exercise must longer than expected üòÇ. Also the numbers don't fit in the circle on Android, not important but a little annoying. With a couple fixes it would be amazing! Love the program so much!!
This app doesn't work properly. It stops and it doesn't have voice you never know when to start again.

I really love this timer. And the work out that goes with it. However on the SS around the 5th excersies you are not counted back in after the rest.. And sometimes you are not counted down.. I think there was a similar problem with the TP. Please fix!!!
I love the concept but just wish it would work without glitching. It doesnt consistently give cues and you have to hold it in front of you to watch the clock. Makes it harder to workout
Glitches and the audio stops 5 minutes into toning power :(
After 3 exercises the voice stops, and the timer itself is glitchy, meaning sometimes 30seconds are actually 15, or on the other hand 60... Not worth.
So simple yet brilliant!!!
Love it!
Great idea but the timer is faulty. Halfway through my workout it no longer announced rest/exercise times and would start and stop randomly.

Ok so alot of people are saying its glitchy and not worth it hut I actually found it extremely helpful. It's really for if you are doing the sweat it to shred it workouts everyday. I have had no problems with it and I think it works very well.
Really gutted. Voice stops after you pause it... Could have continued using my free one to be honest.
Works great!

Love the idea but time COUNTS TOO QUICK AND GLITCHES Really wanted this to be good but the timer counts twice as fast on some setsso you only get half the workout and on specific sets the voice doesn't work so doesn't tell you to start or stop.
It helps to go through the work outs, since is designed for the ebook ‚ù§
Cool idea but as soon as my screen closes then the timer stops working and I have to start over. Really frustrating when 7ou are halfway through a workout
The app is really good up until Sarah doesn't call out how long of the set you have left and then you lose your rhythm
Continues to cut out halfway through my workout. Really annoying that I can't skip to where I was at.

Not very easy to use with pdf, sometimes it lasted longer than the 30 seconds expected and if you had to check it would sometimes be off, then resetting it meant starting again with no way of jumping to the exercise you were on

Not worth the money! It's a very basic timer app with quite some issues. You can pause the timer but the voice will still going and won't be paused. There's no time between exercises to even just switch to the next one, e.g. from crunch to plank, the timer counts down 1 minute and straight goes into counting down the next without any time to switch hence the plank can't be 1 full minute. Really thought it would also tell you the exercise not just exercise 1/2/3 etc. Which is not helpful.
Timer stops talking after 3 excercise intervals. Have to monitor timer because cues stop
I love this app, but the recent update has the numbers a bit screwy. It no longer displays properly when counting down
App crashed during a workout and there is no way to quickly return back to where you were I.e. Go to exercise X and round Y
Sarahs voice disappears after the second round of the first exercise on all workouts :/ kind of defeats the purpose of buying an app so I dont have to watch the clock through my whole workout
downloaded this yesterday and the voice over doesn't work consistently throughout the work out. Very annoying please fix!! I like Sezzy and would like to support her but the app needs to work
Have been using it alongside my Sweat It To Shred It workouts and it has been very easy to use, no bugs, highly recommend!

At round 5 I noticed some of the voice guides missing and by round 6 and 7 there are points where the voice doesn't tell you when the rest period began or ended, nor counting down. Considering I paid money for this it is disappointing that simple voice elements are missing which could have been fixed with a simple proof checking of the app...
After 4th round at first exercise Sarah's voice disappears.. so discouraging paying again for the new version of the app and the story is repeating. :/
App crashes after around two rounds and then you can't resume from where you were. Little bit frustrating.
app keeps crashing during the work out which is super frustrating, please fix!!
great for customisation, but crashed every time I try to use it. Very frustrating :(
game changer!! this app allows you to work out And play music on spotify!!!
App keeps crashing part way through a workout which is very frustrating. Please fix as the app is great other than that
Keeps crashing during workout and I can't press forward to where I was in my workout. Not ideal.

Works great! I had the OG app a while back and this is a vast improvement. I especially love that theres a custom option to build your own circuit workout. My only recommendation is that I wished it showed the total time of the workout. For example the sweaty shredders are about half an hour so itd be nice to see how far you're in time wise. Or if you are creating your own workout you can see how long it would be just in case youre trying to schedule out your gym sesh into your day.
App keeps crashing throughout workouts so I have to restart and figure out which exercise I am up to :( Apart from that though it's great!
